text: Luleå Cathedral () is a cathedral in the town of Luleå in Sweden. It belongs to Luleå Cathedral Parish of the Church of Sweden. It serves the Diocese of Luleå. It was opened in on 3 December 1893. That day was First Advent Sunday the same year. It became a cathedral when the Diocese of Luleå was established in 1904. == References == ==Other websites== Category:Church of Sweden cathedrals Category:Luleå
